FRAUD ALERT: Altegris Winton Futures Fund






























 






























  Free Case Evaluation : 877.238.4175 Tap Here To Call Us   







 
Stock Fraud News & Information

Published By Fitapelli | Kurta





           Stock Fraud News & Information         STOCK FRAUD CLAIMS PRODUCTS PRESS     












Published on: May 22, 2014
Investigation: Altegris Winton Futures Fund

By Fitapelli Kurta






 


Fitapelli Kurta is investigating complaints on behalf of investors who have invested money in the Altegris Winton Futures Fund.  Altegris Winton Future Fund is based in LaJolla, CA and allows investors to invest with as little as $10,000. 
Investigation: Campbell Strategic Allocation Fund
The Altegris Winton Futures Fund is a type of investment fund known as a “managed future fund.”  Many brokers promote managed futures, such as Altegris Winton Futures Fund, as protection against market declines.  However, the language in the prospectuses for these types of funds is not consistent with that notion.  This is not understood by most brokers and investors.
Unbeknownst to many retail investors, Altegris Winton Futures Fund charges institutions that invest at least $1 million a significantly reduced management fee.  Individuals, however, are less fortunate as they are charged higher annual management fees.  Due to this, some of Altegris Winton Futures Fund’s investors lost 10.1 percent in the same period that institutional investors had gains, according to SEC filings.

“Are any of these managed-futures funds worth it anymore at these fee levels?”
– Altegris Executive Vice President Richard Pfister

Managed-futures funds, such as the Altegris Winton Futures Fund, are a subset of hedge funds. The funds are run by commodity-trading advisers, or CTAs.   Although most hedge funds typically charge a 2 percent management fee, managed-futures funds often charge clients 7 to 9 percent of assets invested annually. Altegris Winton Futures Fund charges investors annual fees totaling up to 4 percent according to SEC filings.
If you or someone you know has lost money investing with Altegris Winton Futures Fund, call Fitapelli Kurta at 877-238-4175 for a free consultation. You may be eligible to recoup your losses. Fitapelli Kurta accepts all cases on a contingency basis: we only get paid if and when you collect money. Time to file your claim may be limited, so we encourage you to avoid delay. Call 877-238-4175 now to speak to an attorney for free.














